External links.
SAT problem format.
A SAT problem is often described in the format: an input file in which each line represents a single disjunction. For example, a file with the two lines 
 1 -5 4 0
 -1 5 3 4 0
represents the formula "("x"1 ∨ ¬"x"5 ∨ "x"4) ∧ (¬"x"1 ∨ "x"5 ∨ "x"3 ∨ "x"4)".
